\par <#/>Are civil servants paid by Kanu or are they paid by the tax-payer? <#/>That is a rhetorical question, but it is pertinent and the answer is that civil servants are paid by the tax-payer and tax-payers are not just Kanu members. <#/>Tax-payers are Ken
yans and members of the opposition are also Kenyans who pay tax.
\par <#/>Civil servants must be left alone to make their choices. <#/>To force them to vote for Kanu is to rig the elections. <#/>The elections cannot be free and fair when the imposing posture of
 the PC (<ea/>serikali to most rural folk) tells people who they should vote for.
